                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.1 Polk, Frank L.:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-05T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 5, 1919—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4061. Strictly confidential for the Secretary of State from Polk. Your 3019,
                    September 3. Very many thanks. Quite understand the situation and will follow
                    your advice. I do not look for the slightest friction now. Polk.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
